{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/office-design-by-an-office-hater","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"020314fb-8916-5db5-904b-77262d20d8b7","name":"office-design-by-an-office-hater","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/office-design-by-an-office-hater.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/739F6voYRRdxdY1FTawIgF/c6836334e7ff23bd6e66baa9aa8de063/hero.jpg?w=2048&h=1576","alt":"3-people-office-2k"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I hate offices. I feel uncomfortable in most of them because they are too loud,\ntoo crammed, smell, are too hot or cold. Being a knowledge worker I first and\nforemost need office space that helps me think; but most companies create office\nspace for representative reasons, to impress clients, and show off their\nsuccess, and and not with a focus on the productivity of those tasked with\ncreating this success."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Just last week I was visiting a tech company here in Frankfurt and was shocked\nto discover what the consultants they paid for designing their new interior came\nup with: an open floor plan of randomly distributed work station left and right\nof a walkway and some meeting spots sprinkled within. For me this is madness:\nnot only is there constant sound because of the big open-floor plan, but I also\nget distracted by visual noise: movement. And since the office lacked warm\ncolors, the few unpretentious plants only added to this depressing instance of a\ncreative production line."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"And then I thought, that I‚Äôm making it too easy for myself to just complain. How\nmany interior designers have I heard of, that are coders, too? None. So how can\nI expect them to come up with an office I would work in? Right, I can't."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I think it‚Äôs time that we as software craftspeople, who constantly thrive to\nimprove our skills and tools, start looking at the place where we are practicing\nour craft and take influence in how they are built. We have everything we need\nfor that: I‚Äôve been using 3D tools since I‚Äôm a teenager, I‚Äôve built maps for\nshooters like Doom and Duke Nukem, I‚Äôve been a first-person shooter player for\never. This makes us very well skilled to also think in the physical space of the\noffice world. Not to mention the whole VR thing. The tools we use are more or\nless used in interior design and architecture, and this enables us to speak the\nlanguage of architects and interior designer easily."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Since I recently came around an\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"awesome, browser-based tool"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://spaces.archilogic.com/explore","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" for this\ntask, I set out to create my ideal office. I tried to be very realistic and use\na simple, rectangular floor as the base. I‚Äôve created an office for roughly 30\npeople, because this is known to be optimal team size for humans. Above that\nsize, teams should split up anyway (and move to another floor)."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Because I think that open space floor plans are awful I tried to create as much\nenclosed space as possible, but at the same time enabling everyone to quickly\nsee if a person is busy, available or not even present. Unfortunately glass\nreflects sound very good that‚Äôs why the walls in the offices are made of\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"sound muffling wood panels"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://swedese.com/products/accessories/noton","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":".\nCarpet floors everywhere help with reducing noise further."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#let-me-take-you-through-my-dream-office","ariaLabel":"let me take you through my dream office permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Let me take you through my dream office"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"let-me-take-you-through-my-dream-office","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The base building block is the 3 people office (my favorite!). I think this is\nthe ideal size for day to day work. Every office has tables that are adjustable\nin height electrically and a big (55\") flat screen, for pair programming,\ndisplaying team metrics and doing video calls with those who work remotely."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/739F6voYRRdxdY1FTawIgF/c6836334e7ff23bd6e66baa9aa8de063/hero.jpg?w=2048&h=1576","alt":"3 people office"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Note that a wall shields the tables from the entrance, this reduces visual\nnoise. Teams can also use this wall to hang information about their work, or ‚ÄúDo\nnot disturb‚Äù signs."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/7mT9UHBbgfLoLmzxQMV5A9/75d0d848ad5cace43628e0cb5d225762/office-entrance-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1328","alt":"Office entrance"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Some tasks require bigger groups to work together. Therefore two 6 people office\nrooms exist. They have the same features as the 3 people office."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/1UREL6ipWjH165O0smZZrZ/57882a717cda124fce7d3b60e679a6f8/6-people-office-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1434","alt":"6 people office"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"For one-on-one meetings or just for some quiet alone-time, there are dedicated\nplaces and a nice library."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/6Oz63pNjRtLYgbDmzP95Xf/109393fa7188e3f37642732c0a198f5e/one-on-one-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1302","alt":"One-on-one"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/6vqwFEirgLbP956ALcD1ta/e06d43ed4535c0fd8757c1079a9a0c18/library-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1329","alt":"Library"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"For the daily stand-up everyone can gather in the big open space (the townhall)\nin the middle of the office, which also brings everyone together during lunch\ntime, and can quickly be transformed into a space for meetups. The screens here\nare touch sensitive so you can use it while standing in front of them. Iiyama\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"has those"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://amzn.to/2q9qvoQ","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" or\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"go for the Jamboard"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://gsuite.google.com/jamboard/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" if you can afford it."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/6RZUhGwVScMctLxubCzawW/4f31c02570fb41d67defffd132e60720/townhall-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1329","alt":"Townhall"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"No dedicated meeting room? Yes, meetings should be reduced to an absolute\nminimum and can be held in one of the offices or in the stand-up area. This\nmakes them public and everyone easily has the chance to join in. The same is\ntrue for client meetings, which in my experience rarely take place at the office\nif you are an agency, anyway. So, no dedicated meeting rooms necessary."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The unisex bathroom has a separate shower for those that come to the office by\nbike."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3zwEmp1ZYcfeFhIvSyEGBY/94162ba10f5457c1c41069ec318b0c3e/bathroom-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1331","alt":"Unisex bathroom"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The kitchen is very well equipped with a large stove, because cooking is a great\nsocial activity, and you can't beat healthy, self-cooked lunch."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/7GLZtxVrpTbH35mytKnA0X/ba9630132f351e4429f371a21822443c/kitchen-2k.jpg?w=2048&h=1331","alt":"Kitchen"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You can walk through "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"the plan"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://goo.gl/ewUBFc","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" yourself and even modify\nit with the awesome Archilogic editor."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[],"tagName":"iframe","properties":{"src":"https://spaces.archilogic.com/3d/!768cc6ba-c623-4f8f-9616-ad80515a9322?mode=view&main-menu=interior&view-menu=camera-bookmarks&presentation=loop","width":768,"height":550,"frameBorder":"0","onmousewheel":"false","allowFullScreen":true,"mozallowfullscreen":"","webkitallowfullscreen":""},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"What do you think about this design?"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" Please leave your feedback in the comments."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"And start spreading the word that we as developers are interested in taking part\nin office space design and let me know, how your ideal workplace looks like!"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.0